Unfortunately, we have been relegated to toleration of the bourgeois parties.   
The Schieck Cabinet is re-established, composed only of the [? if not lvp_formed: <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>?][? if stegerwald_path: and [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?]?].

@far_right_coalition_saxony
title: The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">NSDAP</span> enters the governing coalition.
subtitle: Unfortunately, there is no other viable option.
view-if: saxony_no_majority_2
choose-if: mega_bourgeois_coalition_saxony < 50 and far_right_coalition_saxony >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: Even when including the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">NSDAP</span>, the bourgeois government can't find a majority.
on-arrival: saxony_nsdap = 1; nsdap_left += 5; hitler_explode = time + 36; data_miner_detected = 1; workers_nsdap += 6; workers_kpd -= 3; workers_spd -= 2; unemployed_nsdap += 6; unemployed_kpd -= 3; unemployed_spd -= 2; new_middle_nsdap += 4; new_middle_ddp -= 1; new_middle_lvp -= 1; new_middle_spd -= 3; sa_strength += 100; sa_militancy += 0.05; prussian_police_loyalty -= 0.05; pro_republic -= 5; saxony_toleration = 0; saxony_groko = 0; red_saxony = 0; saxony_joever = 0; saxony_spd = 0; saxony_right_2 = 0; saxony_spd_splinter = 0; saxony_soclib = 0; saxony_nsdap_maj = 0; saxony_kpd = 0; saxony_spd_maj = 0
go-to: reichsex_dilemma if president_ideology == "Left" and not presidential_powers
face-image: img/portraits/strasser.jpg

After a failed negotiation previously, the bourgeois parties are now willing to offer a ministerial position to the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> in exchange for their support. Gregor Strasser, leader of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>'s left wing, has been appointed as the new Interior Minister, a role he had been denied in the past due to his more radical anti-capitalist views.

Saxony, once a stronghold of <span style="color: #c00000;">socialism</span> and democracy, is now being dismantled by the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>. The "democratic" aspect more so, as Strasser has pushed for the cabinet to adopt pro-worker and anti-capitalist policies in an attempt to win their votes. The state police, now largely comprised of <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>, are actively suppressing <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> and <span style="color: #700000;">communist</span> organizations and meetings. Socialist newspapers critical of the government have been banned, and civil servants with suspected <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> or <span style="color: #D3C24D;">democratic</span> leanings are being purged in large numbers.

However, there is a real possibility that Strasser could be removed from his position by his coalition partners, as they were never a huge fan of him.

@reichsex_dilemma

President [+ president +] is considering the use of a <i>Reichsexekution</i> to stop the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazi</span> terror in Saxony.  This might risk a civil war, however.  Even if it succeeds, we'll likely just end up in an election loop again.

- @do
- @dont

@do
title: The power of <i>Reichsexekution</i> exists for a reason, and times like this call for it.
subtitle: President [+ president +] will remove Strasser from his post, by force if necessary.
on-arrival: pres_strength = rb_strength*rb_militancy*(1-dissent/2); enemy_strength = sa_strength*sa_militancy + sh_strength*sh_militancy; pres_strength += reichswehr_strength*reichswehr_loyalty*reichswehr_militancy; pres_strength += rfb_strength*rfb_militancy if (president == "Münzenberg" or president == "Thälmann"); pres_strength += rfb_strength*rfb_militancy*(kpd_relation/100) if (kpd_truce or in_popular_front or in_left_front or in_popular_front_prussia or in_left_front_prussia) and president != "Münzenberg" and president != "Thälmann"
go-to: pres_victory if pres_strength >= enemy_strength; war if pres_strength < enemy_strength

@pres_victory
on-arrival: saxony_nsdap = 0; workers_nsdap -= 4; unemployed_nsdap -= 4; new_middle_nsdap -= 4; old_middle_nsdap -= 4; rural_nsdap -= 4; sa_strength -= 100; sa_militancy *= 0.8; coup_progress -= 3; pro_republic += 2; saxony_1933_trigger_time = time + 3

Strasser has backed down!  Unfortunately, as there was no other viable path to a coalition in the Landtag, it will need to be dissolved for new elections once more.

@war
on-arrival: kpd_relation = 65 if president == "Münzenberg" or president == "Thälmann"; kpd_reichsex_sax = 1 if president == "Münzenberg" or president == "Thälmann"

The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span> refuse to acquiesce.  

- @civil_war: This is civil war.

@dont
title: We must not risk a civil war over Saxony.
subtitle: We will let the cabinet stand.

Hopefully Strasser's tenure will prove short-lived.

@true_bourgeois_coalition_saxony
title: The bourgeois parties have garnered a majority to rule via parliament.
view-if: true_bourgeois_coalition_saxony >= 50 and not saxony_right_2
on-arrival: saxony_right_2 = 1; pro_republic += 2; rural_nsdap -= 2; old_middle_nsdap -= 2; rural_other += 2 if dnvp_ideology == "Radical"; old_middle_other += 2 if dnvp_ideology == "Radical"; rural_dnvp += 2 if dnvp_ideology == "Moderate"; old_middle_dnvp += 2 if dnvp_ideology == "Moderate"; saxony_toleration = 0; saxony_groko = 0; red_saxony = 0; saxony_joever = 0; saxony_spd = 0; saxony_nsdap = 0; saxony_spd_splinter = 0; saxony_soclib = 0; saxony_nsdap_maj = 0; saxony_kpd = 0; saxony_spd_maj = 0

Surprisingly, the bourgeois parties have secured a majority all on their own.

The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> is heavily demoralized by this defeat, as they are relegated to the powerless opposition role. They had expected the national political climate to benefit them, and to allow them to influence government.

@united_left_saxony
