Surprisingly,[? if president_ideology != "Left" and not presidential_powers: despite reluctance on both sides due to fears that the <span style="color: #808080;">reactionary</span> President will order a <i>Reichsexekution</i> if a coalition were to form,?] <span style="color: #c00000;">Red</span> Saxony is restored! 

[? if (president_ideology == "Moderate" or president == "Hindenburg") and not presidential_powers: As one of the most left-wing and industrial states in Germany, we will use our leverage to implement comprehensive reforms and transform Saxony into a stronghold of <span style="color: #c00000;">socialism</span>. The President’s patience is especially thin. Tread carefully. ?]
[? if president_ideology == "Left" or presidential_powers: As one of the most left-wing and industrial states in Germany, we will use our leverage to implement comprehensive reforms and transform Saxony into a stronghold of <span style="color: #c00000;">socialism</span>. However, rumors of a far-right coup attempt are growing. Tread carefully. ?]

@president_nope

- @joever

@joever
title: President [+ president +] immediately orders a <i>Reichsexekution</i> against the Saxon government.  
on-arrival: reichsex_sax_trigger = 1

@no_majority
title: No majority can be found!
subtitle: [? if true_bourgeois_coalition_saxony < 50 and spd_coalition_saxony < 50: All possible coalitions lack a majority. ?][? if spd_coalition_saxony >= 50 and not spd_coalition_possible_saxony: The bourgeois parties are antagonistic to our Saxon organization. ?][? if spd_coalition_saxony >= 50 and left_strength >= 20: Our party itself rejects the possibility of a majority coalition with the liberals. ?]
view-if: not saxony_spd_maj and true_bourgeois_coalition_saxony < 50 and (spd_coalition_saxony < 50 or (not spd_coalition_possible_saxony or left_strength >= 20)) and (kpd_r_saxony + sapd_r_saxony) < 50 and nsdap_r_saxony < 50 and spd_r_saxony < 50

With the bourgeois parties unable to secure a majority, and the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> refusing to enter government, the Landtag is in a deadlock. The Schieck Cabinet remains in power as a caretaker government, but a simple majority vote can still dissolve the Landtag, making toleration a necessity.

[? if mega_bourgeois_coalition_saxony >= 50: The coalition of parties in between the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> and the anti-democratic Right constitute a majority, but it is our decision whether or not to tolerate the incumbent government, to prevent new elections from being called. ?][? if mega_bourgeois_coalition_saxony < 50: The coalition of parties in between the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> and the anti-democratic Right don't even constitute a majority, making any majority government impossible. ?]

- @toleration_saxony
- @sapd_aspd_ddp
- @no_majority_2

@no_majority_2
title: A majority still can't be found!
subtitle: [? if mega_bourgeois_coalition_saxony < 50: Even with our votes, it is still joever for the coalition. ?][? if mega_bourgeois_coalition_saxony >= 50: We will refuse to tolerate the bourgeois government, forcing new elections. ?]
view-if: (not saxony_no_majority_2 or far_right_coalition_saxony < 50) 
on-arrival: saxony_1933_trigger_time = time + 3; saxony_no_majority_2 = 1; saxony_no_majority = 1 if not saxony_no_majority; saxony_no_majority += 1 if saxony_no_majority; new_middle_nsdap += 3; old_middle_nsdap += 3; rural_nsdap += 3; unemployed_nsdap += 3; pro_republic -= 3; new_middle_spd -= 2 if toleration_possible_saxony; old_middle_spd -= 2 if toleration_possible_saxony; rural_spd -= 1 if toleration_possible_saxony; reformist_dissent += 10 if toleration_possible_saxony; left_dissent -= 5 if toleration_possible_saxony; saxony_toleration = 0; saxony_groko = 0; red_saxony = 0; saxony_joever = 0; saxony_spd = 0; saxony_right_2 = 0; saxony_nsdap = 0; saxony_spd_splinter = 0; saxony_soclib = 0; saxony_nsdap_maj = 0; saxony_kpd = 0; saxony_spd_maj = 0

With no viable alternatives, the Landtag faces dissolution, triggering new elections—an opportunity the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> hopes to exploit by capitalizing on political instability and the perceived failure of parliamentary democracy.

@spd_majority
title: Form an SPD only goverment!
subtitle: Sweat...
view-if: spd_r_saxony >= 50 and not saxony_spd_maj
on-arrival: saxony_spd = 1; reformist_dissent -= 5; left_dissent -= 30; left_strength += 10; center_dissent -= 10; labor_dissent -= 10; aspd_dead = 1; workers_spd += 7; workers_kpd -= 4; new_middle_spd += 3; old_middle_spd += 2; unemployed_spd += 4; unemployed_nsdap -= 3; pro_republic += 5; saxony_toleration = 0; saxony_groko = 0; red_saxony = 0; saxony_joever = 0; saxony_right_2 = 0; saxony_nsdap = 0; saxony_spd_splinter = 0; saxony_soclib = 0; saxony_nsdap_maj = 0; saxony_kpd = 0; saxony_spd_maj = 1

Unexpectedly, we've found ourselves controlling a majority of the Saxony landtag and being able to form a goverment of just the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>! It is unclear how the bourgeois and <span style="color: #808080;">reactionaries</span> will react to a <span style="color: #c00000;">Red</span> Saxony but without the communists... [? if aspd_share > 0: The ASPD seeing as we no longer require on coalition negoations to form goverment has decided to join us. ?] 
